        <mxCell id="business-rules" value="Business Rules (CORRECTED FLOW):&#xa;&#xa;1. Pre-condition: Appointment status = &#39;reception_approved&#39; (from diagram 03)&#xa;2. Staff navigates to &#39;Chờ thanh toán&#39; (Waiting for Payment) tab in dashboard&#xa;3. Staff sees list of appointments with reception_approved status&#xa;4. Staff clicks &#39;Confirm Payment&#39; button → payment modal opens&#xa;5. Staff selects payment method (cash OR bank_transfer only - 2 types)&#xa;6. Staff enters payment details and uploads proof image&#xa;7. POST /api/service-receptions/:id/confirm-payment&#xa;&#xa;8. KEY: Invoice is created DURING payment processing (confirmPayment function)&#xa;   - Invoice includes: services, parts, external parts, labor, 10% VAT, deposit deduction&#xa;   - Invoice.paymentInfo.status = &#39;paid&#39; (payment already completed)&#xa;   - Transaction record created and linked to invoice&#xa;&#xa;9. Appointment status changes: reception_approved → in_progress (NOT invoiced!)&#xa;10. ServiceReception status changes to &#39;in_service&#39;&#xa;11. Work starts immediately after payment confirmation&#xa;&#xa;12. Invoice display on UI: Just fetch from Invoice table (already complete with all data)&#xa;&#xa;IMPORTANT CORRECTIONS:&#xa;- Invoice is NOT created automatically after reception approval&#xa;- Invoice IS created during payment processing (confirmPayment function)&#xa;- Status goes to &#39;in_progress&#39; NOT &#39;invoiced&#39;&#xa;- Payment methods: Only cash and bank_transfer (2 types)&#xa;- Invoice data is stored in database, not calculated on UI" style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;darkOpacity=0.05;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;align=left;size=10;fontSize=10;" parent="1" vertex="1">
